# Global Colors and Styles

**Glob:** `**/*.css, **/*.tsx`

## Color Usage Policy

All colors in the application MUST use variables from `/colors.css` or `/index.css`. 
Never use raw hex codes, RGB values, or non-existent color variables in the codebase.

## Available Color Variables

Colors in this project use the naming pattern `--BRAND-COLOR-*` or `--GREY-*` (all uppercase with dashes):

- Main brand colors: `--BRAND-COLOR-PRIMARY`, `--BRAND-COLOR-SECONDARY`
- Grey scale: `--GREY-50`, `--GREY-100`, `--GREY-200`, `--GREY-300`, etc.
- Text colors: `--BRAND-COLOR-TEXT`, `--BRAND-COLOR-SUBTEXT`
- Background colors:  `--BACKGROUND-DEFAULT`, `--BRAND-CARD-BACKGROUND-COLOR`

Before creating a new color, check if an existing one can be used.

## ✅ Correct Usage

```css
.my-element {
  color: var(--BRAND-COLOR-PRIMARY);
  background-color: var(--GREY-50);
}
```

## ❌ Incorrect Usage

```css
/* Don't use hex codes directly */
.my-element {
  color: #1976d2;
}

/* Don't use non-existent variables */
.my-element {
  color: var(--primary-main); /* ❌ This doesn't exist in our system */
}

/* Don't use RGB values */
.my-element {
  color: rgb(25, 118, 210);
}
```

## Process for Adding New Colors

If you need a new color, add it to `/colors.css` with proper documentation and get approval from the design team.

